OL,3,CMan accused of stirring up hatred has
OL,4,Ccase moved after wrong charge put to
OL,5,Chim
OL,7,FTim Wilson, who appeared for the
OL,8,Fprosecution, said Mr Boyce had pleaded
OL,9,Fguilty to stirring up racial hatred
OL,10,Funder section 19 of the Public Order
OL,11,FAct 1986 when the charge should have
OL,12,Fbeen for religious hatred under
OL,13,FSection 29C(1).
OL,15,FAndrew Taylor, who appeared for the
OL,16,Fdefence, asked for the case to be
OL,17,Fadjourned. He also said this would
OL,18,Fgive him time to read through
OL,19,Fextensive mitigation documents, which
OL,20,Fhe had just received.
